             sworn. - On the 14th of April I lost a gown; the prisoner nursed my wife; she was taken up on the 5th of May.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18030525-36-person283">
                  ELIZABETH 
                  PENDERGRASS
               <interp inst="t18030525-36-person283" type="surname" value="PENDERGRASS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18030525-36-person283" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18030525-36-person283" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I was lying-in; the prisoner nursed me; I did not miss my gown till I saw it upon her back.</p>
               <p>- DALY sworn. - I am a watchman; Mr. Pendergrass gave me charge of the prisoner; she had this gown on - (producing it.)</p>
               <p>Mrs. Pendergrass. This is my gown; it hung up by the bed-side to darken the room.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. Mrs. Pendergrass lent me the gown to go with her to her mother's.</p>
               <p>Mrs. Pendergrass. I never lent her the gown.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18030525-36-verdict198" type="verdictDescription">
